    <item>
      <title>Immortal - Walkthrough</title>
      <link>https://nvru.github.io/posts/hmv/immortal/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://nvru.github.io/posts/hmv/immortal/</guid>
      
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attacker IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.2&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target Machine IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.20&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The objective was to enumerate the target, identify exposed services, gain initial access through an unrestricted file upload vulnerability, and escalate privileges by abusing writable Python code and a misconfigured &lt;code&gt;systemctl&lt;/code&gt; sudo rule.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://nvru.github.io/images/hmv/immortal/vm.png&#34; alt=&#34;Machine information&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;discovering-the-target&#34;&gt;Discovering the Target&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First, I identified the target IP address on the local network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo arp-scan --interface vboxnet0 --localnet
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Output:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interface: vboxnet0, type: EN10MB, MAC: 0a:00:27:00:00:00, IPv4: 10.10.10.2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;10.10.10.20     08:00:27:13:bb:b5       PCS Systemtechnik GmbH
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;port-scanning&#34;&gt;Port Scanning&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;rustscan&#34;&gt;RustScan&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rustscan -a 10.10.10.20 -- -sC -sV -A -oA nmap/rust
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;results&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;21/tcp open  ftp     vsftpd 3.0.3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;22/tcp open  ssh     OpenSSH 8.4p1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;80/tcp open  http    Apache httpd 2.4.56
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The machine exposed only three services: FTP, SSH, and HTTP.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Yuan111 - Walkthrough</title>
      <link>https://nvru.github.io/posts/hmv/yuan111/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://nvru.github.io/posts/hmv/yuan111/</guid>
      
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attacker IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.2&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target Machine IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.19&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The objective was to enumerate the target, identify exposed services, gain initial access through a Local File Inclusion (LFI) vulnerability, and escalate privileges by abusing a sudo misconfiguration allowing the execution of &lt;code&gt;wfuzz&lt;/code&gt; as root.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://nvru.github.io/images/hmv/yuan111/vm.png&#34; alt=&#34;Machine information&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;port-scanning&#34;&gt;Port Scanning&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;rustscan&#34;&gt;RustScan&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rustscan -a 10.10.10.19 -- -A -oA nmap/rust
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;results&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PORT   STATE SERVICE VERSION
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;22/tcp open  ssh     OpenSSH 8.4p1 Debian 5+deb11u3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;80/tcp open  http    Apache httpd 2.4.62 (Debian)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;HTTP Title:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Rockyou.txt - 密码字典文件介绍
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Only SSH and an Apache web server were exposed, so web enumeration was the obvious next step.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Yuan112 - Walkthrough</title>
      <link>https://nvru.github.io/posts/hmv/yuan112/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://nvru.github.io/posts/hmv/yuan112/</guid>
      
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attacker IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.2&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.18&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The objective was to enumerate the target, identify an XML External Entity (XXE) vulnerability to recover user credentials, gain initial access through SSH, and escalate privileges by abusing an insecure URL validation script executed with sudo.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://nvru.github.io/images/hmv/yuan112/vm.png&#34; alt=&#34;Machine Information&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;port-scanning&#34;&gt;Port Scanning&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;rustscan&#34;&gt;RustScan&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rustscan -a 10.10.10.18 -- -sC -sV -A -oA nmap/rust
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;results&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PORT   STATE SERVICE VERSION
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;22/tcp open  ssh     OpenSSH 8.4p1 Debian 5+deb11u3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;80/tcp open  http    Apache httpd 2.4.62 (Debian)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Only SSH and an Apache web server were exposed, so I began with web enumeration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Yuan113 - Walkthrough</title>
      <link>https://nvru.github.io/posts/hmv/yuan113/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://nvru.github.io/posts/hmv/yuan113/</guid>
      
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attacker IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.2&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.17&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The objective was to enumerate the target, identify exposed services, obtain initial access by enumerating SNMP credentials, and escalate privileges by exploiting an insecure use of Bash&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;declare&lt;/code&gt; builtin in a sudo-allowed script.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://nvru.github.io/images/hmv/yuan113/vm.png&#34; alt=&#34;Machine Information&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;port-scanning&#34;&gt;Port Scanning&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;rustscan&#34;&gt;RustScan&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rustscan -a 10.10.10.17 -- -sC -sV -A -oA nmap/rust
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;results&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PORT   STATE SERVICE VERSION
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;22/tcp open  ssh     OpenSSH 8.4p1 Debian 5+deb11u3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;80/tcp open  http    Apache httpd 2.4.62 (Debian)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Only SSH and HTTP were exposed, so I began enumerating the web application.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Yuan114 - Walkthrough</title>
      <link>https://nvru.github.io/posts/hmv/yuan114/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://nvru.github.io/posts/hmv/yuan114/</guid>
      
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attacker IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.2&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target Machine IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.16&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The objective was to enumerate the target, identify exposed services, exploit a Local File Inclusion vulnerability to obtain credentials, gain SSH access, and escalate privileges through a vulnerable sudo script.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://nvru.github.io/images/hmv/yuan114/vm.png&#34; alt=&#34;Machine information&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;port-scanning&#34;&gt;Port Scanning&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;rustscan&#34;&gt;RustScan&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rustscan -a 10.10.10.16 -- -A -oA nmap/rust
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;results&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Open 10.10.10.16:22
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Open 10.10.10.16:80
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PORT   STATE SERVICE
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;22/tcp open  ssh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;80/tcp open  http
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;nmap&#34;&gt;Nmap&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;nmap -sSCV -A -p22,80 10.10.10.16 -oA nmap/22_80 --min-rate&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1000&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;results-1&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PORT   STATE SERVICE VERSION
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;22/tcp open  ssh     OpenSSH 8.4p1 Debian 5+deb11u3 (protocol 2.0)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;80/tcp open  http    Apache httpd 2.4.62 ((Debian))
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Service Info:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;OS: Linux
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Only SSH and HTTP were exposed, so I focused on web enumeration first.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Jabita - Walkthrough</title>
      <link>https://nvru.github.io/posts/hmv/jabita/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://nvru.github.io/posts/hmv/jabita/</guid>
      
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attacker IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.2&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target Machine IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.15&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The objective was to enumerate the target, identify exposed services, gain initial access through a Local File Inclusion vulnerability, and escalate privileges through sudo misconfigurations and Python library hijacking.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://nvru.github.io/images/hmv/jabita/vm.png&#34; alt=&#34;Machine information&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;port-scanning&#34;&gt;Port Scanning&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;rustscan&#34;&gt;RustScan&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rustscan -a 10.10.10.15 -- -A -oA nmap/rust
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;results&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Open 10.10.10.15:22
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Open 10.10.10.15:80
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PORT   STATE SERVICE
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;22/tcp open  ssh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;80/tcp open  http
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;nmap&#34;&gt;Nmap&lt;/h3&gt;
